In C# you can now write 
```cs
class Sub(int x, int y) : Super(x, y)
{
  public X { get; set; } = x;
  public Y { get; set; } = y;
}
```

which is akin to writing
```cs
class Sub : Super {
  public X { get; set; }
  public Y { get; set; }

  public Sub(int x, int y) : Super(x, y) {
    X = x;
    Y = y;
  }
}
```

